HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 149
BY REPRESENTATIVE LACOMBE
COMMENDATIONS: Commends the Honorable Judge Alvin Batiste, Jr., on the occasion
of his retirement from the Eighteenth Judicial District Court
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the Honorable Judge Alvin Batiste, Jr., on the occasion of his retirement from
3 the Eighteenth Judicial District Court.
4 WHEREAS, the Honorable Judge Alvin Batiste, Jr., has dedicated twenty-three years
5 of distinguished and faithful service as the presiding judge of Division C of the Eighteenth
6 Judicial District Court, and served the citizens of Iberville, Pointe Coupee, and West Baton
7 Rouge Parishes with integrity, fairness, and dedication; and
8 WHEREAS, Judge Batiste further served with distinction as the chief judge of the
9 Eighteenth Judicial District Court and as presiding judge of the Iberville Parish Drug Court
10 for fifteen years and demonstrated a deep commitment to justice, accountability, and
11 rehabilitation; and
12 WHEREAS, Judge Batiste is a proud graduate of the Southern University System;
13 he earned a bachelor of science in economics from Southern University and a juris doctorate
14 from the Southern University Law Center; he was inducted into the Southern University Law
15 Center Hall of Fame in recognition of his outstanding contributions to the legal profession
16 and his community; and
17 WHEREAS, Judge Batiste's career reflects his lifetime commitment to public
18 service, which includes honorable service in the United States Navy Judge Advocate General
19 Corps and roles as an assistant public defender, assistant attorney general, and the first chief
20 administrative officer for Iberville Parish; and
